sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Browser as Web Browser
    participant Route as OpenShift Route
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API
    participant NotebookCtrl as Notebook Controller
    participant Workbench as Jupyter Workbench Pod
    participant MLflow as MLflow Service
    participant S3 as S3 Storage
    participant PG as PostgreSQL
    participant Feast as Feast Service
    participant Redis as Redis Online Store

    Note over User,Redis: Workflow 1: Create Notebook via Dashboard

    User->>Browser: Navigate to Dashboard URL
    Browser->>Route: HTTPS/443 request
    Route->>Dashboard: Forward to kube-rbac-proxy
    Dashboard->>Dashboard: Validate OAuth token
    Dashboard-->>Browser: Show dashboard UI
    User->>Dashboard: Click "Create Workbench"
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: POST Notebook CR<br/>(REST API, SA token)
    K8sAPI->>NotebookCtrl: Notebook CR created event
    NotebookCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create StatefulSet, Service, OAuth client, Route
    K8sAPI->>Workbench: Deploy notebook pod
    Workbench->>Workbench: Pull image from Quay.io
    NotebookCtrl->>Workbench: Inject Feast config via ConfigMap
    NotebookCtrl-->>Dashboard: Notebook ready
    Dashboard-->>User: Show notebook URL
    User->>Route: Access notebook via Route
    Route->>Workbench: Forward request (OAuth Proxy auth)
    Workbench-->>Browser: Jupyter UI

    Note over User,Redis: Workflow 2: Experiment Tracking with MLflow

    Workbench->>Workbench: User runs training script
    Workbench->>MLflow: mlflow.start_run()<br/>(HTTP/5000, Bearer token)
    MLflow->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>(validate permissions)
    K8sAPI-->>MLflow: Authorized
    MLflow->>PG: INSERT experiment metadata<br/>(5432/TCP, TLS optional)
    Workbench->>MLflow: mlflow.log_metric("accuracy", 0.95)
    MLflow->>PG: INSERT run metrics
    Workbench->>MLflow: mlflow.log_model(model, "model")
    MLflow->>S3: Upload model artifacts<br/>(HTTPS/443, AWS IAM)
    S3-->>MLflow: Artifact URL
    MLflow->>PG: Store artifact reference
    MLflow-->>Workbench: Run completed
    User->>Browser: Open MLflow UI (via Istio Gateway)
    Browser->>MLflow: GET /experiments<br/>(HTTPS/443, Bearer token)
    MLflow->>PG: Query experiment data
    MLflow-->>Browser: Experiment results

    Note over User,Redis: Workflow 3: Feature Engineering with Feast

    NotebookCtrl->>Workbench: Inject Feast config at startup
    Workbench->>Workbench: User defines feature views (Python SDK)
    Workbench->>Feast: feast apply<br/>(HTTP/6572, Registry REST API)
    Feast->>S3: Store feature definitions<br/>(HTTPS/443, AWS IAM)
    Workbench->>Feast: feast materialize<br/>(trigger materialization)
    Feast->>PG: Read offline features<br/>(5432/TCP)
    Feast->>Redis: Write to online store<br/>(6379/TCP, TLS optional)
    Note over Feast,Redis: Features materialized<br/>from offline to online store
    Workbench->>Feast: Get training features<br/>(HTTP/80, offline store)
    Feast->>PG: Query historical features
    Feast-->>Workbench: Training dataset
    Workbench->>Workbench: Train model with features
    Note over Workbench: Model deployed (workflow 4)
    Workbench->>Feast: Get online features<br/>(gRPC/6566, online store)
    Feast->>Redis: Fetch features<br/>(6379/TCP)
    Feast-->>Workbench: Online features for inference

    Note over User,Redis: Workflow 4: Platform Installation via DataScienceCluster

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply -f datasciencecluster.yaml
    K8sAPI->>K8sAPI: Webhook validates DSC CR
    K8sAPI->>Dashboard: DSC created event
    Note over Dashboard: ODH Operator reconciles
    Dashboard->>Dashboard: Render component manifests<br/>(Kustomize/Helm)
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: Create Subscriptions for operators<br/>(OLM integration)
    K8sAPI->>K8sAPI: OLM installs operators
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: Deploy Dashboard manifests
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: Deploy Notebook Controller manifests
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: Deploy MLflow Operator
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: Deploy Feast Operator
    K8sAPI-->>User: Components deployed
    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl get datasciencecluster
    K8sAPI-->>User: Status: Ready

    Note over User,Redis: Workflow 5: Idle Notebook Culling

    NotebookCtrl->>NotebookCtrl: Culler loop starts (periodic check)
    NotebookCtrl->>Workbench: GET /metrics<br/>(check activity)
    Workbench-->>NotebookCtrl: Last activity timestamp
    NotebookCtrl->>NotebookCtrl: Calculate idle time
    Note over NotebookCtrl: Idle > CULL_IDLE_TIME
    NotebookCtrl->>K8sAPI: PATCH Notebook CR<br/>(set stopped=true)
    NotebookCtrl->>K8sAPI: Scale StatefulSet to 0
    K8sAPI->>Workbench: Terminate pod
    Dashboard->>Dashboard: Detect notebook stopped
    Dashboard-->>User: Show "Notebook stopped" status
